🔄 Rotate Your Device 🔄
Inside the Dallas studio of sculptor Dan Lam (@sopopomo), burbling, bubbling and bright works of art appear to move on their own. Commissioned by @Genesis_usa, the artist transformed her distinct style into her first-ever digital art car and NFT inspired by her time in the G70. Lam took inspiration from her time driving the G70, and worked with digital designer Stephen Judge (@stephenthejudge) to bring her vision of the world passing outside the windows to life. #G70artcars #GenesisG70 #G70 #artcars #digitalartcars #NFTs #BorntoMove

node.title: Sculptor Dan Lam Blends the Outside World into Her Genesis G70 Art Car

node.text: For this week’s Milkshake, we invited @noznozawa, founder of San Francisco’s Noz Design. Featuring a vessel from @angusandceleste! \\\ #dmtvmilkshake #designmilktv

node.text: Venezuela-born artist @r.sanguino, who works chiefly in ceramics, makes gorgeous, expressive objects. node.text: Modern home wi-fi systems have done an admirable job of disguising their tech in unassuming and non-intrusive housings, designed to blend in to your home while still delivering the connectivity that you need and expect. It’s the same impetus which inspired British industrial product designers Hans Ramzan and Alex Fleming to take a stab at domesticating wi-fi within the home with their own proposed concept, FIVE. "Our mission," says Ramzan, "puts people before technology, humanizing the domestic Wi-Fi system to create the world’s first smart 5G router for the home.” \\\ Read more about FIVE at the link in bio. 🔗

node.text: The process of designing the Burnt Cork collection, an homage to the mountainous areas of Pedrógão Grande that were devastated by forest fires, began in October 2018 when @noeduchaufourlawrance visited a small family-owned cork production facility, NF Cork, in Faro. node.text: Ten years ago, Denmark-based @vipp launched its first kitchen, the iconic black steel V1. With the launch of the new V2 Kitchen, Vipp brings a new palette of materials onboard: Jura marble, a fine grained limestone from Germany’s Alp region, and dark oak, all locally sourced in Europe. The combination of these high-quality materials transforms the Danish kitchen design by taking on a Japanese aesthetic, one that values simplicity and refinement. \\\ Read more about Vipp's V2 Kitchen at the link in bio. 🔗

We’ve long been fans of LA-based artist Joshua Abarbanel, who Design Milk founder @jaimederringer recently started following on the 'Gram (@joshuaabarbanelstudio). "There’s something mesmerizing about his intricate, layered laser-cut wood sculptures that captivate," says Jaime. 

One of his latest pieces, Hull 04 (pictured here in slides 1 and 2), introduces a new material: pulped paper. From Joshua: “The onset of the pandemic crystalized something that I had been wrestling with for a while: feeling inundated by, and guilty about, the copious amounts of paper and packaging materials that suffuse our daily lives. This issue became ever more apparent as quarantine restrictions created a situation where online usurped in-store shopping. Hull 04 starts to address my concerns about privacy, consumerism, consumption and sustainability. The base of this piece is made from the contents of old tax files that I shredded and mulched into paper clay. All of the flourishes on top are made of cut cardboard packing material and product packaging from my household. Hulls—as forms and ideas—reference survival, escape and regeneration.” Also pictured are Abarbanel's works Golem, Seed Field, and Pod01. \\\ Follow Joshua on Instagram or visit the link in our bio to check out more of his work. 🔗

node.text: If what you’re looking for doesn’t exist – design it! That’s what husband and wife team Nick Carmen and Marianne Karaan did with @tokodesign, a simple, functional way to organize your drawers. Inspired by modern furniture, Toko adapts to different drawer sizes and works in every room of your space with clean lines and geometric shapes. It’s even customizable, so you can add in accessories such as a knife block, spice rack or silverware trays to keep things extra tidy. \\\ Read more about Toko at the link in bio. 🔗

node.text: We’ve shared our love of @obakki and their purpose-driven designs before, but their Italian glassware collection deserves a post all its own. To start, it's crafted from Swiss borosilicate glass making it durable against cracking and scratching and resistant to extreme temperature changes. But Obakki’s glassware is special beyond that. It's made by third-generation Italian artisan glassblowers and shaped using traditional mouth blowing techniques. The color palette features shades of deep neutral hues that are sure to mix well with the rest of your bar or kitchen. Perhaps most notably, every single piece is one-of-a-kind. \\\ Read more about Obakki's timeless Italian glassware and shop the collection at the link in bio. 🔗

node.text: Phase Dance is a weekend home located in a dense forest in Shizuoka, Japan. After visiting the undeveloped site a few times, Takeshi Hirobe Architects took interest in a large orange bark stewartia tree and decided to integrate the tree into their building plans. With the tree being center of the construction area, they designed a crescent-shaped house that wraps around the tree, creating a relationship between the two while allowing the greenery the space it needs to flourish. \\\ Read more about this fantastically designed Japanese #treehouse at the link in bio. 🔗
